quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Creating Elements[/h1]

Use the following methods to create new nodes:
[b][/b]element.[b]cloneNode[/b]() clones an element and returns the resulting node.
document.[b]createElement[/b](element) creates a new element node. 
document.[b]createTextNode[/b](text) creates a new text node.

[b]For example:[/b] [code format="js" ]var node = document.[b]createTextNode[/b]("Some new text");[/code]
This will create a new text node, but it will not appear in the document until you append it to an existing element with one of the following methods:
element.[b]appendChild(newNode)[/b] adds a new child node to an element as the last child node.
element.[b]insertBefore(node1, node2)[/b] inserts node1 as a child before node2.

[b]Example:[/b] [code format="html" codeId="958"]<div id ="demo">some content</div>

<script>
  //creating a new paragraph
  var p = document.createElement("p");
  var node = document.createTextNode("Some new text");
  //adding the text to the paragraph
  p.[b]appendChild[/b](node);

  var div = document.getElementById("demo");
  //adding the paragraph to the div
  div.[b]appendChild[/b](p);
</script>[/code]
[note]This creates a new paragraph and adds it to the existing div element on the page.[/note]

